          "text": "Created `DESIGN.md` at the repo root (alongside `SPEC.md`/`ROADMAP.md`).\n\n**What I did:**\n- **Researched the format.** The refero example you flagged is the **ChatGPT** design system — and refero literally exposes a `DESIGN.md` tab. That format is richer than the bare Stitch skill template (adds Surfaces, token tables, and Do/Don't Guidelines), and ChatGPT's monochrome-neutral aesthetic is the *same family* as ours, so I used it as the structural model rather than the thinner Stitch one.\n- **Grounded every claim in real code**, not vibes: read `globals.css`, `components.json`, `layout.tsx`, and the actual `button / input / textarea / card / code-block / markdown / text-shimmer / sidebar` primitives. No fabricated values.\n- **Re-scoped the purpose** away from Stitch (we don't use it) toward AI-codegen + in-repo humans.\n\n**Honest findings baked into the doc:**\n- Our UI is **essentially stock shadcn `new-york` + `neutral`** — pure-grayscale OKLCH, 10px-derived radius, flat elevation. I framed it as deliberate \"neutral minimalism,\" not an unfinished theme, and put the uncomfortable truths in **§12 Open Decisions** (no brand hue, stock baseline, no density profile) so they get chosen rather than drifted into.\n- The genuinely bespoke layers got first-class sections: the **user-switchable font appearance system** (default sans = *system stack*, not Geist; default mono = JetBrains Mono; OpenDyslexic shipped) and **Accessibility** (thick `ring-[3px]` focus, `aria-invalid` pairing).\n\n**Correctness notes:** hex values are labeled as sRGB approximations of the authoritative OKLCH (which is what ships); our neutrals map exactly to Tailwind's neutral ramp; `destructive` = `red-600` ≈ `#e7000b`.\n\nOne thing worth your call: the doc currently documents reality (near-stock). If the real goal is to *define* a llame identity rather than *describe* the shadcn default, that's a brand exercise (§12.1), and a different, bigger task. Say the word.",
